This paper deals with scheduling in distributed and cloud computing, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the optimization of a popular objective function, which is a common topic in Networked Systems (cs.NI) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). The use of a configuration linear program suggests that the paper may also be relevant to Linear and Convex Optimization (cs.LG) and Information Theory (cs.IT).
